  ⚠ react(react-compiler): RenderSetState: Calling setState from useMemo may trigger an infinite loop
    ╭─[react_compiler.tsx:10:7]
  9 │     if (cond) {
 10 │       setPrevItem(item);
    ·       ─────┬─────
    ·            ╰── Found setState() within useMemo()
 11 │       setState(0);
    ╰────
  help: Each time the memo callback is evaluated it will change state. This can cause a memoization dependency to change, running the memo function again and causing an infinite loop. Instead of setting state in useMemo(), prefer deriving the value during render. (https://react.dev/reference/react/useState)

